 basket and set aside the hibiscus water discarding the cooked flowers."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Cheesecake Filling"},{"content":"Place gelatin powder and water into mixing bowl and mix <b>2 sec\/speed 3<b>. Stir with a spatula to ensure all gelatin has dissolved and allow to rest for 5 minutes."},{"content":"Add whipping cream and heat <b>5 min\/195°F\/speed 2<b>."},{"content":"Add cream cheese, sugar and vanilla and mix <b>15 sec\/speed 6<b>."},{"content":"Add raspberries and mix <b>2 sec\/speed 3.5<b>."},{"content":"Pour the cheese filling into the baked crust and add one tablespoon at a time of the hibiscus water, mixing lightly every time you add one tablespoon to get a marbled effect."},{"content":"Refrigerate for 1 hour or until solid."},{"content":"Garnish with additional raspberries. Serve chilled."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Look for dried, edible hibiscus flowers (often called “flor de jamaica”) in specialty shops and Mexican food markets.","Pregnant or nursing women should consult with their physicians before consuming hibiscus."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","2h","8 portions"]}